# PBAC × SpiceDB (server) — CEL caveat `po_limits`
# Policy parameters (active, min_amount, max_amount, regions) are STATIC caveat context on the
# purchase order's governed_by relationship; amount/region arrive at check time.
# Same dataset/IDs as cedar.pbac.http — decisions must match.

@host = http://localhost:8080
@spicedb = http://localhost:8443
@key = benchkey

### ALLOW — via facade (amount inside [min,max], region covered)
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "spicedb",
  "model": "pbac",
  "principal": "psn-091613",
  "action": "po.approve",
  "resource_type": "PurchaseOrder",
  "resource": "po-000160",
  "context": { "amount": 357662180, "region": "bandung" }
}

### DENY — via facade (same PO & amount, region NOT in the policy list)
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "spicedb",
  "model": "pbac",
  "principal": "psn-091613",
  "action": "po.approve",
  "resource_type": "PurchaseOrder",
  "resource": "po-000160",
  "context": { "amount": 357662180, "region": "medan" }
}

### RAW — SpiceDB HTTP gateway with check-time caveat context
POST {{spicedb}}/v1/permissions/check
Authorization: Bearer {{key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "consistency": { "fullyConsistent": true },
  "resource": { "objectType": "purchase_order", "objectId": "po-000160" },
  "permission": "approve",
  "subject": { "object": { "objectType": "persona", "objectId": "psn-091613" } },
  "context": { "amount": 357662180, "region": "bandung" }
}
